The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Sunday, May 30, 2004 				 Pak eases Khan restrictions
				 	 Abdul Qadeer Khan 																								Islamabad, May 29 (Agencies): Pakistan has relaxed the restrictions on its top nuclear scientist Abdul Qadeer Khan who is under house detention after he confessed that he transferred nuclear technology to Libya, Iran and North Korea.																								Khan, known as the father of the Islamic bomb, for his contribution to Pakistans nuclear programme has been allowed to go out of his house in protective custody for one hour a day and meet his family members, local daily Dawn said quoting officials.																								It said that the daughter of Khan, her children and other members of his family had also been allowed to meet him once a day for one hour. Khan, who was subsequently pardoned by President Pervez Musharraf after confessing that he transferred nuclear technology to Libya, Iran and North Korea in violation of the international ban on nuclear proliferation, has been provided regular medical facilities.																								A cardiologist attached to Khan Research Laboratories, (KRL), the countrys premier nuclear installation, has been assigned to look after Khan, the Paper said.																								Khans personal staff along with several nuclear scientists have been detained and questioned after the US and the International Atomic Energy Association (IAEA) forwarded a dossier pointing to their involvement in proliferation of nuclear technology to various countries. 																								While Khan, who was removed as head of the KRL in 2001, was kept under house detention, his personal assistant, retired Major Islamul Haq, along with several top KRL officials were taken into custody. Trader threat																								A Sri Lankan businessman arrested as the suspected middleman in a nuclear parts network run by Abdul Qadeer Khan posed a national security threat, Malaysian Prime Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said today.																								Malaysian resident Buhary Syed Abu Tahir was arrested yesterday in a fashionable suburb of Kuala Lumpur under the Internal Security Act. 
